.IX Item "int table::sort($colID1, $type1, $order1, $colID2, $type2, $order2, ... )"
sort a table in place.
First sort by column \f(CW$colID1\fR in \f(CW$order1\fR as \f(CW$type1\fR, then sort by \f(CW$colID2\fR in \f(CW$order2\fR as \f(CW$type2\fR, ...
\&\f(CW$type\fR is 0 for numerical and 1 for others;
\&\f(CW$order\fR is 0 for ascending and 1 for descending;
